Thanks Alexander. I noticed that one but we have a policy that disallows such changes to the migration scripts.

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/contributing/minor-code-changes.html

Such changes make operators' life painful during migrations.

As far as this one goes, it's debatable to be changed :  the migration scripts are related to swift and the error is actually wrong as the badly formed URI is of swift and not s3.

So, may be we can think of changing that in a different bug & patch (not in this patch) if it is an issue for operators and any strong reason for confusion.
